    "To ensure data representativeness, a random sample of 100 students from various academic areas and levels was selected.",
    "These 100 students were divided into two groups: an experimental group consisting of 50 students and a control group also consisting of 50 students.",
    "The average age of the students is 16 years, with the experimental group comprising 30 women and 20 men, and the control group comprising 28 women and 22 men.",
    "D. Data Collection InstrumentsTo evaluate the quality and accuracy of the content generated with and without the support of ChatGPT, a content analysis method was used, complemented by evaluation rubrics specifically designed for this study (Table 1).",
    "This instrument allowed for a detailed comparison of the research projects completed by the students."
